# Observability Standards

## Structured Logging (Pino / Python loguru)

Every log entry must be JSON with these fields:

```json
{
  "level": "info",
  "time": "2026-01-01T00:00:00.000Z",
  "correlationId": "uuid-v4",
  "tenantId": "string",
  "userId": "string | null",
  "service": "service-name",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "msg": "human-readable message",
  "context": {}
}
```

- Never use `console.log` — always use the configured logger instance
- Never log passwords, tokens, or PII

## Correlation ID

- Generated at the start of every HTTP request
- Propagated to all logs, queued jobs, and outbound calls via `X-Correlation-ID` header
- Stored in `AsyncLocalStorage` (Node) or `contextvars` (Python) — never passed as a parameter

## Health Endpoints (mandatory)

```
GET /health   → 200 always (liveness)
GET /ready    → checks DB + Redis + critical deps (readiness)
GET /metrics  → Prometheus format (latency, errors, throughput per route)
```

## OpenTelemetry

- Configure `@opentelemetry/sdk-node` in bootstrap before server starts
- Auto-instrument: Fastify, Prisma, Redis, BullMQ
- Export to OTLP endpoint via env var `OTLP_ENDPOINT`
- Every span includes `tenantId` and `correlationId` attributes

## Python Experiments

For QML experiment scripts, log at minimum:
- Experiment start: `exp_id`, `model_name`, `started_at`
- Each epoch: `epoch`, `loss`, `accuracy`
- Experiment end: `elapsed_s`, `final_acc`, written to `logs/experiments.jsonl`
